King Hamad bin Isa bin Salman al-Khalifa of Bahrain and Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu of Israel have agreed to establish diplomatic relations and open a new era of friendship and cooperation. They met in Washington at the invitation of President Donald Trump to endorse the principles of the Abraham Accords and promote peace and stability in the Middle East. The diplomatic breakthrough reflects the efforts of the United States to promote peace in the region. The two countries aim to build a future where all peoples and faiths can live together in cooperation and enjoy peace and prosperity. They discussed their commitment to advancing peace and security in the Middle East, recognizing each state's right to sovereignty and a just resolution of the Israeli-Palestinian conflict. They have agreed to establish full diplomatic relations and seek agreements in various areas such as investment, tourism, security, and technology. They also express their appreciation to President Trump for his efforts in furthering peace in the region.